17 13–5602.
18 (a) There is a Population Health Improvement Fund.
19 (f) (1) Subject to [paragraph] PARAGRAPHS (2) AND (3) of this subsection,
20 the Fund may be used only for expenses associated with statewide population health
21 improvement initiatives in alignment with the statewide health equity plan as directed by
22 the Secretary.
23 (2) Activities paid for by the Fund must support the goal of meeting the
24 statewide population health targets outlined in the AHEAD Model State Agreement with
25 the Center for Medicare and Medicaid Services and have at least one of the following
26 functions:
27 (i) Reducing rates of common preventable health conditions;
28 (ii) Addressing health–related social needs; or
29 (iii) Reducing or eliminating health disparities.
30 (3) THE DEPARTMENT AND THE HEALTH SERVICES COST REVIEW
31 COMMISSION MAY TRANSFER MONEY FROM THE FUND TO THE PUBLIC HEALTH
32 WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT FUND ESTABLISHED UNDER § 24–2802 OF THIS
33 ARTICLE.
34 SUBTITLE 28. PUBLIC HEALTH WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT FUND.

HOUSE BILL 1109 13
1 24–2801.
2 IN THIS SUBTITLE, “FUND” MEANS THE PUBLIC HEALTH WORKFORCE
3 DEVELOPMENT FUND.
4 24–2802.
5 (A) THERE IS A PUBLIC HEALTH WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT FUND.
6 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO SUPPORT THE EDUCATION AND
7 TRAINING OF THE PUBLIC HEALTH WORKFORCE.
8 (C) THE MARYLAND COMMUNITY HEALTH RESOURCES COMMISSION
9 SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUND.
10 (D) (1) THE FUND IS A SPECIAL, NONLAPSING FUND THAT IS NOT
11 SUBJECT TO § 7–302 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
12 (2) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL HOLD THE FUND SEPARATELY,
13 AND THE COMPTROLLER SHALL ACCOUNT FOR THE FUND.
14 (E) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:
15 (1) MONEY APPROPRIATED IN THE STATE BUDGET TO THE FUND;
16 (2) INTEREST EARNINGS OF THE FUND;
17 (3) ANY MONEY TRANSFERRED FROM THE POPULATION HEALTH
18 IMPROVEMENT FUND UNDER § 13–5602 OF THIS ARTICLE; AND
19 (4) ANY OTHER MONEY FROM ANY OTHER SOURCE ACCEPTED FOR
20 THE BENEFIT OF THE FUND.
21 (F) THE FUND MAY BE USED ONLY TO SUPPORT THE EDUCATION AND
22 TRAINING OF THE PUBLIC HEALTH WORKFORCE.
23 (G) (1) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL INVEST THE MONEY OF THE FUND
24 IN THE SAME MANNER AS OTHER STATE MONEY MAY BE INVESTED.
25 (2) ANY INTEREST EARNINGS OF THE FUND SHALL BE CREDITED TO
26 THE FUND.

