25 (a) (1) There is a Maryland Corps Program Advisory Board.
26 (2) The Advisory Board consists of the following members:
27 (i) a Board Chair, appointed by the Governor;
28 (ii) two members jointly appointed by the President of the Senate
29 and the Speaker of the House:

HOUSE BILL 1109 15
1 1. one of whom must represent a service organization in the
2 State; and
3 2. one of whom shall be:
4 A. a current participant in a public service program; or
5 B. a former participant in a public service program whose
6 participation ended during the preceding 3 years;
7 (iii) one member appointed by the President of the Senate;
8 (iv) one member appointed by the Speaker of the House; and
9 (v) [four] FIVE members appointed by the Governor[,]:
10 1. one of whom shall be a representative from the Maryland
11 State Service Commission; AND
12 2. ONE OF WHOM SHALL BE A HEALTH OFFICER, AS
13 DEFINED IN § 1–101 OF THE HEALTH – GENERAL ARTICLE.
14 (b) In making appointments to the Advisory Board, the President, Speaker, and
15 Governor shall consider:
16 (1) the professional or personal experience of the individual in community
17 or other service, nonprofit management, civic engagement, or volunteerism;
18 (2) the cultural, geographic, racial, ethnic, and gender diversity of the
19 State; and
20 (3) an individual’s experience and knowledge in workforce development,
21 including regional workforce needs, training, career development programming, and
22 workforce investment boards.
